data.name: DispatchDescriptor
desc: describes a feature to be retrieved by a URL that has to be loaded into a specified frame

For a normal dispatch calls all needed parameters are separated. For optimized remote functionality XDispatch.queryDispatches() it's necessary to pack these parameters in a flat structure which can be used in a simple manner.

properties.name: FeatureURL
desc: specifies the URL of the resource/function
Must be a full parsed URL. Use service com.sun.star.util.URLTransformer for that.

properties.name: FrameName
desc: Special targets (e.g. \"_blank\", \"_self\") or really existing target names can be used.

properties.name: SearchFlags
desc: describes how the target frame is to be searched
This optional parameter is used if FrameName isn't a special target only.
